current_subtask:
  summary: Fix the one-tap import completion race found by the real phone workflow.
  root_cause: The picker change handler calls routeTo('#/add') even though the consumer is already on ADD; the core can rebuild the view and detach #importWorkbenchHost before completion renders.
  current_ci:
    - overlay validation: success on head c280c04
    - kernel parity: success on head c280c04
    - phone onboarding/import: failed waiting for the Reddit completion panel
    - Pages build: in progress on head c280c04
  fix:
    - remove the redundant route from importChosen
    - keep the existing mounted workbench alive throughout import
    - make both phone tests surface error-panel text immediately instead of timing out invisibly
  done_when: Both real iPhone journeys reach Reddit completion, remain quiescent, and the deliberate OPEN MY FEED transition loads the imported record.

